         <abstract>
            <p>Recurrence relations of the form $$a_rp_{r + 1} = b_rp_r + c_rp_{r - 1}$$ are examined in two cases: (A) oscillatory systems, for which $b^2_r + 4a_rc_r &lt; 0$; (B) monotonic systems, for which $b^2_r + 4a_rc_r \geq 0$. In both cases, a posteriori methods are supplied for constructing strict and realistic error bounds in $O(r)$ arithmetic operations. A priori bounds, also requiring $O(r)$ arithmetic operations, are supplied in Case B. Several illustrative numerical examples are included.</p>
          </abstract>
